HEADWORD: Impracticability
<hw>Im*prac`ti*ca*bil"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Impracticabilities</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The state or quality of being impracticable;
infeasibility.</def> <rj><au>Goldsmith.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An impracticable thing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Intractableness; stubbornness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impracticable</ent>⟦br⟧
